msgctxt "sn22.120:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:0.2"
msgid "12. Dhammakathikavagga "
msgstr "12. A Dhamma speaker "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 120. Saṃyojaniyasutta → saññojanam (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.120:0.3"
msgid "120. Saṃyojaniyasutta "
msgstr "120. Things Prone To Being Fettered "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.167, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.2"
msgid "“Saṃyojaniye ca, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi saṃyojanañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the things that are prone to being fettered, and the fetter. "

msgctxt "sn22.120:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.4"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā, katamaṃ saṃyojanaṃ? "
msgstr "What are the things that are prone to being fettered? And what is the fetter? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.5"
msgid "Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyo dhammo; "
msgstr "Form is something that’s prone to being fettered. "

msgctxt "sn22.120:1.6"
msgid "yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ. "
msgstr "The desire and greed for it is the fetter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.7"
msgid "Vedanā … pe … "
msgstr "Feeling … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.8"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "Perception … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.9"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "Choices … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.10"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ saṃyojaniyo dhammo; "
msgstr "Consciousness is something that’s prone to being fettered. "

msgctxt "sn22.120:1.11"
msgid "yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ. "
msgstr "The desire and greed for it is the fetter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.12"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā, idaṃ saṃyojanan”ti. "
msgstr "These are called the things that are prone to being fettered, and this is the fetter.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.120:1.13"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

